N:skill-standardization
D:Standardize and validate SKILL.md files against the Agent Skills specification (agentskills.io). Use when creating new skills, auditing existing skills for spec compliance, improving trigger descriptions, consolidating duplicates, or checking drift between live skill folders, shipped discovery surfaces, and compact variants like SKILL.toon / SKILL.compact.md. Triggers on: validate skill, create SKILL.md, standardize skill format, check skill spec, improve skill description, catalog sync, skills.json drift, SKILL.toon drift.
G:skill-management standardization validation agentskills-spec automation description-optimization
U[8]:
  Creating a new SKILL.md from scratch
  Auditing existing skills for spec compliance
  Converting legacy skill formats to standard structure
  Improving descriptions for better triggering accuracy
  Adding evaluation test cases (evals/evals.json)
  Batch-validating all skills in a directory
  Auditing skills.json / README / setup inventory drift against live folders
  Auditing SKILL.toon / SKILL.compact.md drift after material rewrites
S[4]{n,action}:
  1,Validate SKILL.md with scripts/validate_skill.sh
  2,Check catalog drift with scripts/validate_catalog_sync.py and review compact variants
  3,Create or fix SKILL.md frontmatter and sections
  4,Write effective description with imperative phrasing and trigger keywords
